name: Dennis Crowley
bio: I like to build things (@Foursquare📱, @StockadeFC ⚽️, @StreetFC, Dodgeball 📟) Husband to @Chelsa & Dada to 👧🏼🧒🏼&👶🏼. Splitting time btw NYC & Kingston

social_posts.post_text:
Hey these pics are 9 months old (March 2022!) but on the eve of our first day of the 2023 ski season (tomorrow!) I gotta share how much progress Marsy (@4yo) made last year… and really the *last 4 days* of the season last year.  He was uninterested/uninspired most of the season even tho we tried everything (m&ms, leash, edgie-wedgie, hot chocolate, hula hoop) but then SNAP! he just had this amazing “if my sister can do it, then I can do it too” moment one day and it just CLICKED with him. In four days we went from “not gonna happen, maybe next year” to “omg he’s almost too fast too keep up with” and it just brought me *so much joy*. I’m posting this tonight so I can show him these photos in the morning and say “remember buddy? We LOVED this!” to get him fired up.  Btw, if you’re struggling with this phase, remember this Best Ski Advice Ever (which I got from my brother): “Your job is not to teach them how to ski, your job is to get them to love skiing”. 👍🏼❤️🥰

ps: yes these are my skis (and pants!) from 1990 (before I switched to snowboarding). I was able to teach Via while on the board (thx to help from @katieccollins) but had to WAX UP THE STIX to get Marsy out.  Will be on skis tomorrow (started mixing it up w skis / snow skate / showboard). #CrowleySkiSchool

We built this pretty rad thing called @StreetFC — think: Soul Cycle but for pickup soccer games, played in spots that feel like Street Fighter or Tony Hawk levels.  It’s pretty rad, you should come to a game sometime!  We’re live in ~10 cities and hosting 100+ games/month.  Our whole team is in NYC this week so we did a Staff Game and team dinner. 👍🏼⚽️

Going on a ski trip with buddies!  We’ll be in Jackson Hole for a few days — our first ski trip since pre-COVID!  While this photo is not from Jackson, and not from a trip with same buddies, this is the level of *fired-up* I am as I Uber to the airport! (Baldface 2015 btw…. this pic just resurfaced on Google Photos and it’s too rad not to post)

In January 2007 (16 years ago!) I saw *this picture* in an issue of Forbes Magazine and I ripped it out hung it on my fridge. “Someday we’re gonna ski that” I told my buddies.  In 2008, we made our first trip to Jackson Hole, WY to scout it out (“Corbet’s Coulier”). We returned again in 2009 and 2019 to try to ski it.  On all 3 trips it was always either closed or too sketch to ski.  We’re back here now — our 4th trip out — and I finally got a good-enough day to try and drop in. *This* has been the #1 on thing in my bucket list for YEARS and I’ve carried this weight of “I just gotta ski this thing” for as long as I can remember.  Drop in was sketch, but rode it out clean. I cried like a baby at the bottom, just psyched to cross this off my list after so many years.  Special thx to @willmcd for shooting an epic video (volume up! 🔊) and @jcrowley and @uffal and BCollins and @xtianbovine for egging me on (and all your patience!) all these years.  ps: Last pic is us scouting it for the first time back in 2008. (and yeah, gonna try to ski it again today because I think I can ride that intro line cleaner/faster)

We took another look at Corbet’s yesterday, but just as we got there Ski Patrol ⛑️ closed it down (see the patroller in the background?) …. and I was fine with that :) Will be excited to come back and do this again — different line / different drop. I’d still like to be able to do this top-to-bottom without a stop (in the video yesterday, I had to drop down onto the “goat path” before dropping into the chute… but I think you need a good powder day for that). Btw, ski patroller was telling us that Corbet’s got shut down at 12:30p the day I skied it — and our photos are timestamped 12:11p so I juuuuuuussstt made it. Whew! 😅 Fun trip and super thankful for both our ski crew and our wives who are holding down the fort back at home. xo @chelsa! ❤️

Just realized my brother-in-law Brian had this alternate angle of the Corbets drop.  I trimmed the middle 20 seconds where I was being all wishy-washy about whether to drop in regular or switch (um, once I dropped in, I realized the plan I made before the drop was not gonna work, ha!) Thx for capturing Brian! (and if you wait till the very end you can see where @willmcd was standing when he took his video… yikes!)

2023 ski season recap — We’ve now got 3 kids on snow (um, even tho Sammy at 20mo only lasted about 5 minutes). Via @ 6.5yo is ripping with swagger on skis and just started linking turns on a snowboard (!!), while Mars @ 5yo can both stop and turn (even though he rarely chooses to do either). Getting out on snow with the kids has led to some of the most rewarding moments I’ve had as a dad, and as a partner to @chelsa (“look at this squad of little rippers we made!” — xo sqz!). Shoutout to my mom & dad for all the help with Sammy (which allowed us to ski with the kids, and sometimes make no-kids runs too). Via racked up 23 days on snow which is both awesome and crazy, so here’s to even more runs (and Sammy joining the pic!) in 2024. #CrowleySkiSchool

OMGoodness look what I found in my Instagram drafts… pics from last years Sink or Skim (ahem, pond skimming!) at Mount Snow (2022). Long story short — after 3 failed attempts over the last 10+ years (um, I sank), I *FINALLY* cleared it last year. And yes, if you’re gonna do it you gotta dress up. 🤵🐸 @chelsa gave it a shot too… and when she wiped out a few yards before the pond, she took the advice I gave her just in case such a catastrophe was to occur… “just fall on your sword” (lolz!) and so she just sunsetted herself  into the pond (lolz lolz!). This is super fun and one of my fav weekends at Mount Snow. Was bummed to miss it this year! 📸 Epic photo of me mid-skim in a tux from ⛑️ Ski Patroller @feldmanpt (thank you!)
Just found this pic of Mars in my camera roll and I love it. From @carparknyc event last October (2022)

Hey V, Mars and SamSam, you are *so lucky* to have the raddest, kindest, sweetest, bestest, most badass and most fun mama of all time. (and I’m so lucky I get to raise 3 kids with her!) ❤️ xo sqz! (and yes, this is my fav pic of you from last year :)

I hope I never ever forget how much this little baby just LOVES ME TO PIECES.  She is so much fun and we have such an amazing little bond right now (20mo old). Third baby just hits different 😘 Reach for the stars, SamSam! 🚀
Sammy exploring.

Happy 2nd birthday to my sweetest little SamSam. You are an endless source of energy and laughter and love and you *absolute compete* our little Party of Five. You have a crazy advanced vocabulary for a 2yo, you speak with a sing-song in your voice (“i waNNA watch TV”), you know exactly how to use your eyes to be expressive/manipulative (and your side-eye is wild), and you have me absolutely wrapped around your finger (“i waNNA eat dadas cereal”). Your sister *adores* you, you love yet bully your brother (but he still gives you a kiss goodnight sometimes), and mama and dada just feel so blessed to have you in our lives. Before you went to bed tonight I gave you 1 kiss, 1 nuzzle, 1 hug-with-a-pat, 10 spiders, and a pigeon ice cream cone. ❤️🥰
Day vs night, August 2023.  Our first family hike (!!) … and then 10 hours later (after kids are zzz) laying outside with @chelsa looking for shooting stars. ❤️💫

Sammy (2yo) has the weirdest bedtime routine — I read her books and we play a game or whatever, but she doesn’t want me to put her to bed. So I kiss her goodnight and tell her she can stay up a few more minutes and I dim the lights super low. Within 2-3 mins she’ll get off the couch, check to make sure door is closed, and then climb into her bed and tuck herself in. It’s super cute,  but also super sad since I want to give her a tuck-tuck like the other kids. 🥲💤
Sammy vs cookie. ❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️ (Volume up! 🔉)

Found this drone + ATV footage I filmed a few years ago (@skydiohq drone btw). Trails are a bit overgrown now (3 years!) but just started cutting them back again so we can use them with the kids (hikes and bikes and ATVs)
The sweetest @ 2yo.

My boy with the beautiful brain started drawing these sketches recently — they’re a mix of cords and pipes and electricity and batteries and clocks and maps and networks.  He is the most interesting little kid I’ve ever met — can’t wait until he can teach me more about the way he sees the world. 🥰

A few weeks ago me & C celebrated 10 years married (!!) Time flies when you got a Chrysler Pacifica full of kids!  Here’s 10 years worth of anniversary nights out — you’ll see many of them feature a bottle of our wedding wine (the wine we gifted our guests) which we force ourselves to drink every year :) Hey #sqz, xoxo and psyched for the next 10 years of adventures ❤️😘

Long story short — we lost this beautiful giant Asian Elm tree a few years ago. Tree was maybe 150+ years old?  The kids were super fond of the tree (it had an awesome swing on it), and it didn’t feel right to just get rid of it (it’s been there forever!), so we worked with @newyorkheartwoods to turn it into a dining room table!  The table is *stunning* (so much so that we’re about to renovate the dining room so it matches the awesomeness of the table). Also this sunset (Sept ‘22) was pretty badass.  ps: table is 10 feet long!

So excited to get these poohs back out on the snow again. This is one of my all-time fav pics of Mars btw, *losing his mind* because he got the Gold Chair at @mountsnow (“gold is my favorite color!”). Via is in the devo program this year so she’ll be taking ski lessons every weekend (!!) and we expect she’ll be *ripping* by the end of the season (I think she’s gonna ski in the AM and snowboard in the PM, which is badass IMHO). Sammy… we’re gonna try to get her out this year.  She asks to see this pic *all the time* (“I wanna see Sammy skiing!”) not realizing/remembering that she was obviously not having a great time.  In the wise words of my brother “your job isn’t to make them ski, your job is to make them to love skiing”
We did it!  Mars was smitten. Via was shy. Sammy was like “oh hell no” 🤣  Happy holidays everyone!

Three kids on skis, a Babcie and Diggie who are around to lend a hand, and a house full of siblings & cousins… we’ve got a lot to be thankful for. That is all! (ps:  ask me about the last pic, where Sammy’s too-big-for-her boots fell off while we were riding the lift. Both skis, both boots, and one little sock 🤣  Oh, and Via snowboards now too because she’s a badass. 🤙
